&lt;p>CSS&amp;rsquo;s Three Main Features: Inheritance, Cascading, Specificity&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="inheritance">Inheritance
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>Child elements inherently pick up text-related properties from their parents. If a child has its own styles, it won&amp;rsquo;t inherit those specific properties.&lt;/p>
